To build this IT service ticketing tool in OutSystems 11, you will leverage OutSystems Entities (Database Tables), Web Screens (User Interfaces), and Forms / Blocks (Reusable UI components).
OutSystems automatically generates the standard User entity for you, so you will build your business data model around it.
------------------------------
## 🏛️ OutSystems Data Model (Database Entities)
In OutSystems, tables are called Entities, and columns are called Attributes. You will create the following core entities in your Database layer:
## 1. Ticket (Entity)
Stores the core details of every IT request.

* Id (Identifier, Auto-number)
* Title (Text, Mandatory)
* Description (Text)
* StatusId (Static Entity Identifier: New, Open, In Progress, Resolved, Closed)
* PriorityId (Static Entity Identifier: Low, Medium, High, Critical)
* ServiceTypeId (Static Entity Identifier: Software, Hardware, Network, IT Support)
* CategoryId (Category Identifier FK - e.g., Laptop Repair)
* RequesterUserId (User Identifier FK - automatically linked to OutSystems system User)
* AssignedAgentUserId (User Identifier FK, Nullable)
* CreatedOn (DateTime, Default: CurrDateTime())
* ClosedOn (DateTime)

## 2. Category (Entity)
A lookup table to organize sub-issues based on the service type.

* Id (Identifier)
* ServiceTypeId (Static Entity Identifier)
* Name (Text - e.g., "Password Reset", "OS Installation", "Broken Screen")
* IsActive (Boolean)

## 3. TicketComment (Entity)
Tracks communication history and internal notes.

* Id (Identifier)
* TicketId (Ticket Identifier FK)
* UserId (User Identifier FK - author of the comment)
* Message (Text, Mandatory)
* IsInternalNote (Boolean - True if only visible to IT agents)
* CreatedOn (DateTime)

## 4. Static Entities (Enums)
Create these as Static Entities in OutSystems for hardcoded, fast-loading dropdown values:

* TicketStatus: New, Open, In_Progress, Resolved, Closed
* TicketPriority: Low, Medium, High, Critical
* ServiceType: Software, Hardware, IT_Support, Network

