## 🖥️ Application Screens (UI Web Screens)
You will organize your screens into distinct flows. Use Role-based Security in the screen properties to restrict access.
## 1. End-User Portal Flow (Role: Registered Users)

* EmployeeDashboard: A clean page featuring an aggregate list of "My Active Tickets" and "My Historical Tickets". Includes a prominent button to "Raise a New Ticket".
* NewTicket: A dedicated page featuring the ticket submission form.
* UserTicketDetail: A conversation-focused view where the employee can see status updates, read agent replies, and add new comments.

## 2. IT Agent Console Flow (Role: ITAgent)

* AgentQueue: A master dashboard utilizing an OutSystems Table Records widget or a custom Kanban Block to show unassigned tickets, open tickets, and high-priority software/hardware queues.
* AgentTicketDetail: A robust, split-screen UI. The left side displays user profile details and asset information. The right side features a chat timeline for communication, toggleable tabs for public replies vs. internal agent notes, and a sidebar for shifting ticket metadata.

## 3. Admin Management Flow (Role: ITAdmin)

* AdminDashboard: A metrics view displaying charts (using OutSystems Charts) tracking open tickets by Service Type, average resolution time, and agent workloads.
* ConfigurationManager: Simple CRUD (Create, Read, Update, Delete) screens to manage sub-categories (e.g., adding a new category under "Hardware").

