## 📝 Essential OutSystems Forms & Blocks
Use the Form widget in Service Studio to automatically map screen inputs to your Entity variables.

* Form_NewTicket (End-User):
* Inputs: Title (Input), ServiceTypeId (Dropdown), CategoryId (Dropdown - configured with a Refresh Data action to dynamically filter based on the selected Service Type), Description (TextArea), Attachment (Upload Widget).
* Form_TicketUpdate (Agent Sidebar):
* Inputs: StatusId (Dropdown), PriorityId (Dropdown), AssignedAgentUserId (Dropdown populated by a query of users with the ITAgent role).
* Block_CommentSection (Reusable Component):
* A custom OutSystems UI Block containing a List Records widget for displaying history and an input layout for typing a response. For agents, it includes a Switch widget mapped to IsInternalNote.
